Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` for the hardware/software back button:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget since the override is synchronous
            ShowUnsavedChangesDialog();
            return true; // Cancel navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async void ShowUnsavedChangesDialog()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**2. Replace the Shell back arrow with a custom "Cancel" toolbar item:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- Or inline: -->
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}"
                            IconOverride="" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
</ContentPage>
```

**3. Wire up the command (in your ViewModel or code-behind):**

```csharp
// Code-behind approach:
public EditProductPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();

    var backBehavior = new BackButtonBehavior
    {
        TextOverride = "Cancel",
        Command = new Command(async () =>
        {
            if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");
                if (!leave) return;
            }
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        })
    };

    Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, backBehavior);
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **Android hardware back** button and returns `true` to cancel navigation.
- `BackButtonBehavior` with `Command` intercepts taps on the **Shell navigation bar back button** and replaces it with your "Cancel" text.
- You need **both** — `BackButtonBehavior.Command` doesn't fire for the hardware back button, and `OnBackButtonPressed` doesn't affect the nav bar button.
- **iOS swipe-back gesture**: set `IsEnabled = false` on `BackButtonBehavior` to disable it when there are unsaved changes, since the swipe gesture bypasses both handlers.
